  "doc_id": "37418",
  "text": "Portable, hand-held dental radiometers are inexpensive and simple to use. Radiometers have many disadvantages. Their accuracy was reported to be sensitive to the diameter of the light guide tip [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In addition, they cannot continuously monitor the light output over the irradiation time [CITATION_3] . Also, they only indicate the existence emitting tip irradiance and not the irradiance of the light cure unit when held at a distance from the radiometer [CITATION_4] .",
